parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger failure can cause loss of power, white smoke from the exhaust, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Oil cooler failure can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure.
EGR valve failure can cause the check engine light to illuminate, and potentially lead to engine damage.
Engine sludge can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deployment of airbags without a crash, causing injuries or fatalities, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates intermittently or remains on
the airbag deploys without a crash
the passenger airbag light comes on when the ignition is turned on and stays on
the airbag warning indicator stays on whether a passenger is on the seat or not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has led to a shortage of replacement parts, causing delays in repairs and leaving vehicle owners without a functioning airbag system, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The part needed to repair the airbag system is unavailable
the manufacturer exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
the vehicle owner is unable to get the recall repair done due to lack of parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control and brake systems can lead to loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal is stiff and will not disengage
the cruise control will not turn off when the brake pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the roof-mounted fit kit can cause the rack and load to come loose while driving, creating a potential road hazard and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The bolt(s) used to secure the foot to the vehicle was manufactured to a hardness that may cause the bolt(s) to be brittle and potentially break under stress.
